"Here is the motivation thread designed to weave through your academic paper:\n\n**CORE_NARRATIVE**: \nLight field depth estimation remains fundamentally bottlenecked by the pervasive \"texture-copy\" artifact in non-Lambertian regions, a catastrophic failure that stems not from a lack of network capacity, but from the field's over-reliance on the flawed view-consistency assumption. By shifting the paradigm from heuristic photo-consistency to wave-vector-level angular frequency physics (via MRI-like 2D-DFT and dual-mask modeling), we can explicitly decode material spectral signatures and eliminate these artifacts at their physical root. This approach replaces uniform depth constraints with adaptive, material-aware priors, bridging the critical gap between idealized diffuse benchmarks and complex, real-world mixed-material scenes.\n\n**INTRO_HOOK**: \nOpen by challenging the field's \"elephant in the room\": while current light field depth estimation methods perform exceptionally well on diffuse objects, they catastrophically fail on the glass, metal, and glossy surfaces that dominate real-world scenes. Highlight the direct consequence—the jarring \"texture-copy\" artifact—and boldly state that no amount of scaling network capacity will fix this until the fundamental, yet flawed, view-consistency assumption is discarded.\n\n**GAP_BRIDGE**: \nTransition from related work by framing previous deep learning approaches as \"symptom-suppressors\" that try to smooth over artifacts post-hoc, rather than diagnosing the physical disease. Establish the critical pivot for your method: to solve this, we must look below pixel-level intensities and analyze the angular domain through Maxwell's equations and wave-vector theory, extracting physical priors via k-space frequency analysis.\n\n**METHOD_JUSTIFY**: \nFrame the introduction of your 2D-DFT, dual-mask mechanism, and GCD/SAM strategy as physical necessities rather than arbitrary architectural choices. Justify that because diffuse, specular, and scattering materials inherently exhibit distinct spectral signatures (low-frequency dominance vs. high-frequency broadening), physics demands a system that classifies materials via medium/directional masks and applies differentiated energy adjustments (like the ternary-mask strategy) rather than treating all angular blocks equally.\n\n**EXPERIMENT_VALIDATE**: \nStructure your results section to act as a direct proof of your core claim, prioritizing visual and quantitative evidence of texture-copy artifact elimination over sheer benchmark dominance. Explicitly showcase the massive contrast ratio improvements (e.g., Apple scene jumping from 1.35 to 33.8) to prove that modeling wave-vector physics physically separates true depth structure from smooth non-Lambertian surfaces better than any data-driven heuristic.\n\n**CONCLUSION_ECHO**: \nConclude by reasserting that overcoming the view-consistency assumption is the master key to unlocking robust 3D reconstruction and AR in unconstrained, real-world environments. End with a forward-looking call to the community: future depth estimation models must be grounded in explicit, physically interpretable wave-vector analysis rather than brute-force scaling of fundamentally flawed heuristics."